I better head inside soon.

264
00:27:59,303 --> 00:28:03,724
Thank you for the meal, <i>Eonni.</i>
Can you keep this a secret from my mom?

265
00:28:05,351 --> 00:28:07,561
You got it. Don't worry about it.

266
00:28:11,941 --> 00:28:13,317
-Oh, <i>Eonni</i>.
-Yes?

267
00:28:13,526 --> 00:28:15,319
What's your phone model?

268
00:28:15,903 --> 00:28:17,530
-My phone?
-Yeah.

269
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:22,284
Hello. I'm Yoon Seol-a from Bongcheong
Elementary, third year, third class.

270
00:28:22,493 --> 00:28:23,494
One second.

271
00:28:26,414 --> 00:28:28,916
Hmm. Should we
tuck your hair behind your ears?

272
00:28:31,210 --> 00:28:33,796
Nah, it was better before.
Let's try it again.

273
00:28:34,255 --> 00:28:35,840
Please introduce yourself.

274
00:28:36,048 --> 00:28:40,094
Hello. I'm Yoon Seol-a from Bongcheon
Elementary, third year, third class.

275
00:28:40,177 --> 00:28:42,346
Yoon Seol-a <i>yang,</i>
why do you want to be a singer?

276
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:44,765
Um…

277
00:28:45,474 --> 00:28:49,228
CANCER HOSPITAL
HEART AND BRAIN HOSPITAL

278
00:29:00,698 --> 00:29:05,119
How dare you meet up with this
filthy undertaker when your baby is sick!

279
00:29:08,789 --> 00:29:10,666
I'll take care of the baby.

280
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:13,627
Thank you, I'll only take a moment.

281
00:29:30,269 --> 00:29:33,022
How do you dance so well, by the way?
Where'd you learn?

282
00:29:33,105 --> 00:29:34,482
K-pop star fancams.

283
00:29:35,065 --> 00:29:38,819
My classmates only get to watch if they
get a good grade on the English test

284
00:29:38,903 --> 00:29:40,946
but my mom knows nothing other than money.

285
00:29:41,030 --> 00:29:44,617
Money, money, money.
But still complains about not having any.

286
00:29:46,452 --> 00:29:47,995
Is this your phone number?

287
00:29:48,412 --> 00:29:51,332
Yeah. Call me if you need to
take videos of anything else.

288
00:29:51,957 --> 00:29:52,958
I'll think about it.

289
00:29:54,126 --> 00:29:56,629
We're here. I live right there.

290
00:29:59,715 --> 00:30:00,841
Go ahead inside.

291
00:30:04,970 --> 00:30:06,805
-Hey, <i>Eonni</i>.
-Yeah.

292
00:30:07,097 --> 00:30:10,643
-I'm good at singing, too.
-Whoa, really?

293
00:30:10,726 --> 00:30:13,354
I have to take a video
of the singing as well.

294
00:30:13,812 --> 00:30:16,440
Can you help me with that, too?

295
00:30:17,399 --> 00:30:23,864
Oh… But what do I do?
I have to head back to work for now.

296
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:28,244
Um… Would it be okay to
meet up next week again to do that?

297
00:30:29,161 --> 00:30:32,122
I'd like that!
I should practice until then.

298
00:30:32,998 --> 00:30:34,083
Thank you, <i>Eonni.</i>

299
00:30:35,251 --> 00:30:36,252
Take care.

300
00:30:49,932 --> 00:30:51,850
<i>Oh, because Joon-ho told me</i>

301
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:55,646
<i>to ask a police officer</i>
<i>if I can't find the ring.</i>

302
00:31:02,194 --> 00:31:03,195
What's up?

303
00:31:13,622 --> 00:31:19,837
By chance… Do you know of anyone that was
at Joon-ho's accident at the time?

304
00:31:21,297 --> 00:31:23,591
-Who?
-Maybe like a police officer.

305
00:31:26,010 --> 00:31:29,305
Hm… There must have been.

306
00:31:30,681 --> 00:31:32,391
A first responder.

307
00:31:33,434 --> 00:31:35,394
Right, first responder…

308
00:31:38,939 --> 00:31:39,940
Why do you ask?

309
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,652
Just curious about the incident.

310
00:31:43,986 --> 00:31:47,531
-Anything else from the investigation?
-Well…

311
00:31:48,824 --> 00:31:51,327
You must know that
it was dark and had no passerby's

312
00:31:51,869 --> 00:31:54,788
so they weren't transported
to the hospital right away.

313
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:59,460
You must also know that
a man living nearby reported it.

314
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:04,673
Also that he got caught at the scene
so there's nothing else to investigate.

315
00:32:08,010 --> 00:32:12,014
-Is something wrong?
-Oh, no.

316
00:32:23,275 --> 00:32:25,069
HANGEUL PROCLAMATION DAY
9

317
00:32:55,182 --> 00:32:59,645
My goodness, until when do I have to
look after this idiot…

318
00:33:10,239 --> 00:33:11,782
MAKE THIS FOR YOUR SISTER 
WHEN SHE GETS HERE.

319
00:33:41,478 --> 00:33:42,479
Mom…

320
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,581
Wow.

321
00:34:00,664 --> 00:34:02,374
Starting with handmade <i>mandu</i>

322
00:34:02,791 --> 00:34:04,376
Mother prepared everything.

323
00:34:04,626 --> 00:34:06,462
Everything you like. Right?

324
00:34:07,796 --> 00:34:10,174
You saw, I didn't touch a single dumpling.

325
00:34:10,257 --> 00:34:12,092
So please tell our mom that, <i>Noona</i>.

326
00:34:13,260 --> 00:34:15,220
-Now then, shall we dig in?
-Yes.

327
00:34:16,346 --> 00:34:17,473
Thank you for the meal.

328
00:34:31,904 --> 00:34:33,030
You should have this.

329
00:34:39,328 --> 00:34:43,123
What is this, conveyor belt sushi?!
Just serve yourselves!

330
00:34:46,084 --> 00:34:47,085
Uncle.

331
00:34:48,879 --> 00:34:50,130
Thank you, my nephew.

332
00:34:55,886 --> 00:34:59,515
-Mm. The ribs are amazing.
-Are they?

333
00:35:11,527 --> 00:35:12,528
<i>I…</i>

334
00:35:13,821 --> 00:35:16,406
<i>I-I think I got top grade in the class.</i>

335
00:35:16,490 --> 00:35:20,244
-First place in the police academy!
-Oh man! You did?

336
00:35:20,911 --> 00:35:25,040
Top of the class are promised assignment
to the department of their choice…

337
00:35:26,208 --> 00:35:28,961
Oh man, we're done struggling, <i>Hyeong.</i>
Good job!

338
00:35:31,004 --> 00:35:33,090
I thought, for once in my life

339
00:35:36,426 --> 00:35:39,471
something called "happiness" was coming.

340
00:35:40,305 --> 00:35:42,933
I uh, can't let today go by.

341
00:35:44,184 --> 00:35:47,396
-Hey, let's drink.
-I wish you would stop drinking

342
00:35:47,813 --> 00:35:49,523
<i>and just get married.</i>

343
00:35:49,606 --> 00:35:52,317
W<i>hat do I own that I</i>
<i>would find love and get married?</i>

344
00:35:52,401 --> 00:35:55,487
I'm a mess with a rap sheet 
instead of a high school diploma,

345
00:35:55,737 --> 00:35:58,740
<i>an alcoholic father</i>
<i>who kicked the bucket in prison,</i>

346
00:35:59,074 --> 00:36:01,702
and a mom that was
on the news when she passed.

347
00:36:08,917 --> 00:36:10,377
<i>I'm done for,</i>

348
00:36:10,961 --> 00:36:12,754
so just worry about yourself.

349
00:36:14,339 --> 00:36:17,092
Man, how are you our father's son?

350
00:36:19,136 --> 00:36:20,762
Is there a mistake somewhere?

351
00:36:24,141 --> 00:36:25,642
I think I'm also done for.

352
00:36:55,714 --> 00:36:57,758
Are your parents here?

353
00:37:00,761 --> 00:37:04,681
I bet they were very happy
to see you for the first time in a while.

354
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:11,146
It must have been two years.

355
00:37:21,907 --> 00:37:23,909
A parent who have lost their child

356
00:37:27,412 --> 00:37:29,331
are alive, but not alive at all.

357
00:37:33,919 --> 00:37:36,672
Their insides empty, about to crumble away

358
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:39,466
even if they are alive, they are dead.

359
00:37:42,219 --> 00:37:43,220
I…

360
00:37:49,476 --> 00:37:51,436
I must have done that to my parents, too.

361
00:37:55,732 --> 00:37:57,859
But even then,
just because I'm their child

362
00:38:02,072 --> 00:38:06,743
they are so sorry that I am hurt.

363
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:12,374
Even though they're dead, themselves.

364
00:38:23,719 --> 00:38:24,886
Compared to that

365
00:38:28,724 --> 00:38:30,642
I'm really going through nothing.

366
00:38:31,351 --> 00:38:33,061
I felt so terrible about that

367
00:38:38,233 --> 00:38:39,526
I couldn't endure it.

368
00:38:46,491 --> 00:38:48,660
You said, sorry
that you ran away, right?

369
00:38:57,836 --> 00:39:00,338
I couldn't even
keep him company on his way.

370
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:05,260
Neither could I keep my parents company.

371
00:39:05,343 --> 00:39:06,845
DECEASED KIM JOON-HO <i>NIM</i>

372
00:39:11,683 --> 00:39:12,976
<i>It's me that ran away.</i>

373
00:39:18,982 --> 00:39:20,817
Do you know

374
00:39:22,569 --> 00:39:24,696
what one hears the most
at a funeral?

375
00:39:26,406 --> 00:39:28,366
"If you're alive, you should live."

376
00:39:31,620 --> 00:39:35,791
I thought that was
such a cruel thing to say.

377
00:39:38,627 --> 00:39:39,628
But

378
00:39:43,590 --> 00:39:46,218
The Deceased's tell me the same thing.

379
00:39:49,096 --> 00:39:50,972
To keep those left behind alive.

380
00:39:52,474 --> 00:39:54,267
To make it less painful for them.

381
00:40:01,108 --> 00:40:02,234
So…

382
00:40:07,322 --> 00:40:08,323
Please live.

383
00:40:10,450 --> 00:40:12,119
You should live too, Tae-hee <i>ssi.</i>

384
00:40:15,580 --> 00:40:16,581
Stay alive

385
00:40:20,043 --> 00:40:21,044
and remember him.

386
00:40:26,133 --> 00:40:28,468
People say that if someone is remembered

387
00:40:30,303 --> 00:40:34,432
they are not completely gone,
even if they pass.

388
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:43,817
<i>Please give this to Joon-ho.</i>

389
00:40:44,693 --> 00:40:47,612
<i>Make sure to tell him tomorrow</i>

390
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:51,783
<i>that there are this many people</i>
<i>who remember him.</i>

391
00:41:01,793 --> 00:41:04,212
How come you're out in the cold?

392
00:41:05,630 --> 00:41:07,507
I'm so full, I had to digest a bit.

393
00:41:08,967 --> 00:41:11,803
It's great eating Mom's food
for the first time in so long.

394
00:41:14,139 --> 00:41:17,559
I asked you to visit us so many times.
How could you not come once?

395
00:41:18,101 --> 00:41:19,102
I'm sorry.

396
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:34,492
Mom.

397
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:36,161
Hm?

398
00:41:44,669 --> 00:41:48,006
What's the occasion?
Holding your mom's hand like that.

399
00:41:49,341 --> 00:41:51,343
Was my food that good?

400
00:41:58,850 --> 00:42:00,310
Let's go together, tomorrow.

401
00:42:06,650 --> 00:42:08,735
Yeah, let's.

402
00:42:18,119 --> 00:42:20,247
Joon-ho would be so excited tomorrow.

403
00:42:20,997 --> 00:42:23,875
To meet Mom, Dad and <i>Hyeong </i>all together.

404
00:42:39,891 --> 00:42:43,395
DECEASED KIM JOON-HO

405
00:42:46,898 --> 00:42:50,610
Joon-ho, your mom's here.

406
00:43:58,303 --> 00:44:00,930
{\an8}-GOOD NIGHT!
-YES, HAVE SWEET DREAMS.

407
00:44:17,072 --> 00:44:19,866
<i>It went well. I'm back now.</i>
<i>Thought you might be worried.</i>

408
00:44:38,218 --> 00:44:41,596
It'll be a long trip
driving all the way down there again.

409
00:44:42,931 --> 00:44:45,433
Let's get going before rush hour.

410
00:44:45,517 --> 00:44:47,060
-Yes, we should.
-Oh, the bag.

411
00:44:51,481 --> 00:44:52,774
Take care of yourself.

412
00:44:55,860 --> 00:44:56,861
Goodness.

413
00:44:58,446 --> 00:45:00,031
Don't worry about me. Okay?

414
00:45:03,785 --> 00:45:06,246
Come on, families aren't supposed to be
like this.

415
00:45:06,329 --> 00:45:09,082
-Stop it, stop. Stop I say.
-Let's go.

416
00:45:09,624 --> 00:45:13,211
-Drive safe.
-<i>Maehyeong, </i>go ahead. Get going, go, go.

417
00:45:15,672 --> 00:45:17,257
Oh, Hae-an! Come over here.

418
00:45:18,925 --> 00:45:20,009
Come over, come over!

419
00:45:22,762 --> 00:45:24,305
He's on our second floor.

420
00:45:25,348 --> 00:45:28,560
Say hi. This is my older sister
and brother-in-law<i>.</i>

421
00:45:28,768 --> 00:45:30,937
Therefore, Kim Tae-hee <i>gun</i>'s parents.

422
00:45:32,939 --> 00:45:34,732
-Hello.
-Yes, nice to meet you.

423
00:45:36,067 --> 00:45:39,112
-Oh, right! His home town is <i>Yeosu, </i>too.
-I see.

424
00:45:39,195 --> 00:45:42,157
That's an hour away from where we live.
Where in <i>Yeosu?</i>

425
00:45:44,784 --> 00:45:46,870
-G-Gwangmu District.
-Ohh.

426
00:45:47,328 --> 00:45:49,038
-Heading to work?
-Yes.

427
00:45:50,081 --> 00:45:54,377
I really gotta get to work now. I'll
make sure to properly meet you next time.

428
00:45:54,461 --> 00:45:56,087
-I'll be going now.
-Work hard!

429
00:45:56,171 --> 00:45:57,464
-Will do!
-Alright.

430
00:45:59,007 --> 00:46:00,425
Go home now, shoo.

431
00:46:00,508 --> 00:46:03,011
Maehyeong, go ahead now. Go, go.

432
00:46:37,003 --> 00:46:38,004
<i>Seong-nim!</i>

433
00:46:40,381 --> 00:46:42,675
-Hey.
-What brings you all the way here?

434
00:46:46,304 --> 00:46:47,722
Wanted to give you this.

435
00:46:54,979 --> 00:46:56,940
You should, uh, dress warmer.

436
00:46:57,565 --> 00:46:59,150
You'll catch cold like that.

437
00:47:05,114 --> 00:47:06,491
What's with the silence?

438
00:47:07,492 --> 00:47:08,701
Are you blown away?

439
00:47:12,914 --> 00:47:15,833
I've never in my life
received anything like this…

440
00:47:18,336 --> 00:47:19,837
Thank you, <i>Haeng-nim.</i>

441
00:47:28,012 --> 00:47:29,013
Hae-an.

442
00:47:29,847 --> 00:47:30,932
Yeah?

443
00:47:37,188 --> 00:47:38,523
I like Dong-joo <i>ssi.</i>

444
00:47:43,319 --> 00:47:44,320
We're dating.

445
00:47:51,035 --> 00:47:56,499
Oh… It must have been you
that Dong-joo <i>ssi </i>likes.

446
00:48:04,674 --> 00:48:06,968
Letting days go by without telling you

447
00:48:12,390 --> 00:48:15,560
felt like a mistake to me.
That's why I'm telling you.

448
00:48:17,395 --> 00:48:18,980
I bet you'll feel betrayed

449
00:48:21,441 --> 00:48:22,609
You may hate me…

450
00:48:25,278 --> 00:48:27,572
Seo Hae-an.
Come here for a sec.

451
00:48:28,948 --> 00:48:30,408
Oh, go ahead.

452
00:48:40,043 --> 00:48:41,044
<i>Seong-nim.</i>

453
00:48:43,254 --> 00:48:45,673
You don't have to be so sorry about it.

454
00:48:48,009 --> 00:48:49,010
I…

455
00:48:51,179 --> 00:48:52,555
I really like you.

456
00:48:54,474 --> 00:48:55,975
I'm always on your side.

457
00:48:59,312 --> 00:49:02,440
Thank you so much for this.
I'll wear it with care.

458
00:49:02,899 --> 00:49:04,525
No problem. Go on inside.

459
00:49:06,277 --> 00:49:07,278
Okay.

460
00:49:08,363 --> 00:49:09,489
I'll be going then.

461
00:49:24,253 --> 00:49:25,254
Oh?

462
00:49:26,673 --> 00:49:30,551
You're the Eonju Uni Hospital
Emergency Room Doctor, right?

463
00:49:30,635 --> 00:49:32,637
I'm Seol Hyun-yong,
from investigations.

464
00:49:32,929 --> 00:49:35,098
Oh… Hello.

465
00:49:35,181 --> 00:49:39,018
You know, back when I used to
get dispatched to ER every other day

466
00:49:39,102 --> 00:49:42,188
All other doctors
gave me the cold shoulder

467
00:49:42,271 --> 00:49:44,273
but you alone were friendly to me.

468
00:49:44,899 --> 00:49:45,900
I remember you.

469
00:49:47,527 --> 00:49:49,028
I heard the news.

470
00:49:49,487 --> 00:49:51,864
That you left the hospital
after the incident.

471
00:49:53,616 --> 00:49:56,369
I was assigned your brother's case.

472
00:49:57,745 --> 00:49:58,746
What?

473
00:50:00,164 --> 00:50:01,874
There was no time to say hi.

474
00:50:01,958 --> 00:50:04,001
Your father came for statements

475
00:50:04,711 --> 00:50:07,505
I actually did see you at the ER that day.

476
00:50:08,423 --> 00:50:10,007
You were probably not yourself.

477
00:50:10,091 --> 00:50:13,052
-Did you by chance go to the site, too?
-The site?

478
00:50:13,261 --> 00:50:16,347
First responder was
dispatched from the police box. Why?

479
00:50:16,931 --> 00:50:19,350
I'm wondering
if there were any words from them.

480
00:50:19,434 --> 00:50:23,730
When he got there, they were on their way
to the ER already despite the late report.

481
00:50:26,649 --> 00:50:28,359
The bastard's still in hospital, right?

482
00:50:33,531 --> 00:50:36,367
-Yes.
-Man, he better not die like that.

483
00:50:36,868 --> 00:50:39,162
Drunk drivers need to be punished hard.

484
00:50:39,620 --> 00:50:40,830
If he dies…

485
00:50:44,917 --> 00:50:47,170
-Will the case close?
-Yeah.

486
00:50:48,504 --> 00:50:50,631
If he dies, it all ends.

487
00:51:04,228 --> 00:51:08,900
<i>When he got there, they were on their way</i>
<i>to the ER already despite the late report.</i>

488
00:51:56,906 --> 00:51:59,367
Yes, Eonju University Hospital
Funeral Home.

489
00:52:12,171 --> 00:52:15,174
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

490
00:52:15,258 --> 00:52:19,720
Is it… Possible to
do the coffining at night?

491
00:52:21,264 --> 00:52:25,935
I mean, it's just… I think it'd be better
to get it over with sooner than later.

492
00:52:26,686 --> 00:52:29,856
I see. Well, I will take a look at
our schedule and let you know.

493
00:52:32,942 --> 00:52:34,110
